



Sir
Boston 6 June 1776



Inclosed is the Invoice of the Ordnance Stores which I have forwarded to Norwich to the Care of Capt. Huntington to be forwarded from thence by him to New york, agreeable to General Putnams request in his letter to me of the twenty fourth of May.1 All those Articles were taken in the Ship Hope lately brought into this Harbor by Captain Mugford. I am Your Excellencys Obedient Humble Servant

Artemas Ward

